## Tools & Resources

### Building UTMs
**UTM Builder:** Use https://ga-dev-tools.google/campaign-url-builder/ to generate properly formatted URLs

### Shortening URLs (Highly Recommended)

Long UTM URLs look messy in social posts. Use URL shorteners to create clean links while preserving all tracking.

**Bitly (Recommended):**
- https://bitly.com
- Free tier available (50 links/month)
- Custom slugs (e.g., `bit.ly/sr-demo-feb1`)
- Additional click analytics
- Link management dashboard

**TinyURL:**
- https://tinyurl.com
- Completely free, unlimited
- Simple and fast

**Rebrandly:**
- https://www.rebrandly.com
- Custom branded short domains (e.g., `stonerise.link/demo`)
- Professional appearance
- Requires paid plan for custom domains

### URL Shortening Workflow

**LinkedIn Note:** LinkedIn automatically shortens URLs over 23 characters using its own `lnkd.in` shortener. While this preserves UTM parameters, using a custom short link (Bitly/TinyURL) gives you better control over the slug name and provides additional click analytics.

**Step 1:** Build your complete URL with all UTM parameters
```
https://www.stonerise.tech/request-demo?utm_source=linkedin_michael&utm_medium=organic_social&utm_campaign=invoice_ai_procurement&utm_content=20260203_post1
```

**Step 2:** Go to Bitly and paste the FULL URL (with all UTMs)

**Step 3:** Create a custom slug like `sr-demo-feb03`

**Step 4:** Get your short URL
```
https://bit.ly/sr-demo-feb03
```

**Step 5:** Use the short URL in your social post

**CRITICAL:** Always shorten the FULL URL including all UTM parameters. Never shorten just the base URL, as this would lose all tracking data.

**Example Post:**
```
Really pleased with how Invoice AI has come together.

[...post content...]

Drop me a message if you want to see it in action, or book a demo here: https://bit.ly/sr-demo-feb03
```

The short link redirects to the full URL with all UTM parameters intact, so you get clean posts AND complete tracking.

**Note on utm_content format:** Always use `YYYYMMDD_post[N]` for organic social posts (e.g., `20260203_post1` for February 3, 2026, first post). This provides precise date tracking and sorts naturally in analytics.

